<body>

  <h1>Task 1: HTML, CSS, and JS Fundamentals</h1>

  <section>
    <h2>Objective</h2>
    <p>Understand the foundational concepts of web development using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>1. HTML (Structure)</h2>
    <p>Use HTML to create the basic structure of a webpage.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Use elements like <code>&lt;div&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;p&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;a&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;img&gt;</code>, etc.</li>
      <li>Structure content with semantic tags like <code>&lt;header&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;section&gt;</code>, and <code>&lt;footer&gt;</code>.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="code-box">
&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
  &lt;head&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;My Page&lt;/title&gt;
  &lt;/head&gt;
  &lt;body&gt;
    &lt;h1&gt;Welcome!&lt;/h1&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;This is a paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>2. CSS (Styling)</h2>
    <p>Use CSS to style the content and layout of the page.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Apply colors, fonts, spacing, and responsive design.</li>
      <li>Use selectors, classes, and IDs effectively.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="code-box">
body {
  background: #f0f0f0;
  font-family: Arial;
}

h1 {
  color: #3498db;
}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>3. JavaScript (Interactivity)</h2>
    <p>Use JavaScript to add interactivity to your webpage.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Respond to user events like clicks and form inputs.</li>
      <li>Manipulate the DOM and use basic logic/loops.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="code-box">
document.getElementById("btn").onclick = function() {
  alert("Button clicked!");
};
    </div>
  </section>

</body>
</html>
